anti-templating cross-check:
  C7 lead: 6-April-2025 cliff framing ("The remittance basis ended on 6 April 2025
    under Finance Act 2025 s.40 and Schedule 9"); H2 architecture organised around
    cliff + FIG + TRF + rebasing + LTR + four-deep-dive routing.
  C8 lead: solo-occupant statutory specifics ("If you live alone, your council tax
    bill is reduced by 25% under LGFA 1992 s.11(1)(a)"); H2 architecture organised
    around mechanic + Schedule 1 disregards + application + 21-day discipline +
    overpayment-review defence. Distinct from C9 reference framing.
  C9 lead: eleven-disregard architectural framing ("The single-person council tax
    discount under LGFA 1992 s.11(1)(a) reduces a dwelling's council tax bill by 25%
    where only one non-disregarded adult is resident. Schedule 1 lists categories of
    adult who are disregarded for this purpose"); H2 architecture organised around
    full s.11 + Schedule 1 + SI 1992/558 + sole-or-main-residence doctrine +
    cross-jurisdictional + historical evolution + policy critique. Reference-grade
    framing, distinct from C8 operational framing.
  C10 lead: two-concept-distinction primer framing ("UK tax residence and UK domicile
    are two distinct legal concepts. From 6 April 2025, UK tax residence drives income
    tax and CGT under the Statutory Residence Test"); H2 architecture organised around
    SRT cascade + split-year + LTR + property-investor angles + departure/arrival
    planning windows + residual operation of domicile.
  C11 lead: reframing framing ("An estate-agent's 'free rental valuation' is a
    marketing appraisal, not a tax-defensible valuation document"); H2 architecture
    organised around two-product distinction + eight tax / compliance use-cases +
    below-market-rent family scenario + how-to-commission + firm role.
  C12 lead: four-tax-stack framing ("Selling a house at below market value is
    analytically a partial sale plus partial gift"); H2 architecture organised around
    each tax separately + s.53 connected-company trap + PPR + spouse exemption +
    valuation evidence + dispute route + worked examples.
  Six distinct H1/H2/voice profiles, no templating drift detected.

cannibalisation discipline notes:
  C7 / C10 paired:
    C7 = historical-context hub ("what ended on 6 April 2025"). Routes to existing
    FIG / TRF / rebasing / Year-5-cliff deep-dives.
    C10 = current-architecture hub primer ("how UK tax residence and domicile work
    now"). Routes to same four deep-dives PLUS C7. Differentiation explicit in both
    pages: C7 opens with the cliff; C10 opens with the two-concept distinction. C7
    body references "what UK tax residence now does"; C10 body references "what the
    remittance basis was before it ended" (one paragraph each, no overlap).
  C8 / C9 paired:
    C8 = operational applicant ("how to apply"). Step-by-step + evidence + 21-day +
    overpayment defence.
    C9 = architectural reference ("complete guide"). Full s.11 + each Schedule 1
    disregard in operative detail + sole-or-main-residence doctrine + cross-juris +
    historical + policy critique. Explicit body cross-link: C8 routes reader to C9
    for "the complete statutory architecture"; C9 routes reader to C8 for "the
    operational how-to-apply primer". No content overlap on the doctrinal sections
    or on the application-procedural sections.
  C11 / C12 paired:
    C11 = Red Book valuation evidence primer. Eight use-cases for Red Book.
    C12 = four-tax stack for partial-sale-partial-gift. Uses Red Book valuation as
    its evidence pillar. Explicit body cross-link: C11 routes reader to C12 for
    "the chargeable consideration thread on below-market sales"; C12 routes reader
    to C11 for "the Red Book vs estate-agent appraisal distinction". No content
    overlap on either the valuation methodology or the four-tax computation.

